File> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];                    // Array of content files being processed\n  output: Map<string, string>;             // output path → rendered HTML\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;             // output path → binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;              // Shared plugin data store for inter-plugin communication\n}\n\nexport interface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;                            // URL-friendly identifier\n  title: string;\n  content: string;                         // Raw content (markdown or HTML)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;       // Custom metadata\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. BUILD ENGINE (src/core/engine.ts - 117 lines)\n\n**Key Capabilities:**\n\n- **Plugin Registration**: `registerPlugin(plugin)` - adds plugins to execution queue\n- **Template Registration**: `registerTemplate(template)` - registers reusable templates\n- **Topological Sort**: `resolvePluginOrder()` - uses DFS to order plugins by dependencies\n  - Detects circular dependencies\n  - Detects missing dependencies\n  - Returns plugins in correct execution order\n- **Build Process** (`async build(files)`):\n  1. **beforeBuild** phase - all plugins in dependency order\n  2. **transformContent** phase - each file goes through transformContent hooks in plugin order\n  3. **Template Rendering** - applies templates to files, outputs to `ctx.output`\n  4. **afterBuild** phase - all plugins in dependency order\n  - Returns populated `BuildContext`\n\n**Build Flow Example:**\n1. Create BuildContext with empty output/assets/data maps\n2. Order plugins via topological sort\n3. Call beforeBuild on each plugin\n4. For each file, 